    {
      "id": "4014319459da0684c2afd0d4b58169767833a795",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2015-10-14 23:04:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAlex has your concern been meet for the latest patch?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "f41f5bd9aa128241dd8d128bfa546c240e92ded2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2015-10-19 07:11:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI don't think so - calling iget() within a running transaction is a known issue.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "35101d30d4b67db80de66599d9ee06b7dc7631fc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-10-22 23:43:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nMaybe we can use oic_cache, i.e. add inode into the oic_cache in declare, the only problem here is that oic_cache is supposed to share between threads, but we want to release those inode in env_exit for each thread.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "7499cdd8794d4344116c23be7b09287b1c3dc1f1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2015-10-23 09:20:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI'm not a big fan of doing this, but you can add struct inode * to osd_thandle and release it in osd_trans_stop()",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "3311776e0617430450dfcffb826ebcd043ce5e19",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-10-26 08:04:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n\"I'm not a big fan of doing this, but you can add struct inode * to osd_thandle and release it in osd_trans_stop()\"\n\nI think there is an issue if we cache this inode in declare index insert(), because if it is creation, then this inode is not being created yet in declare phase, that said this extra effort in osd_declare_index_ea_insert() is most likely useless,( osd_oi_lookup() will most likely return -ENOENT)\n\nSo it basically add an uselss oi lookup in create process. IMHO, it is not a good idea. Any other suggestion?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "f4abe59650b45e06c2435184376deda442cd14ab",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2015-10-26 13:16:55.000000000",
      "message": "Removed the following approvals:\n\n* Code-Review+1 by James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
